{"id": 4983, "title": "Ticket #4983: condor_submit should allow setting of attribs BEFORE submit is parsed", "description": "<blockquote>\nthe <code>condor_submit -append</code> statements are only applied once the queue statement is read, this makes it impossible to use them in if clauses in the submit file.  So a way is needed to pass on the command line attrib values that happen before the submit file is parsed.\n\n<p>One way to do this would be to treat loose arguments that contain an = as attrib=value pairs rather than interpreting them as the name of the submit file.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Apr-22 09:15</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/0568c233b6cd65d20ba885f4933753aada7e65b7\">[44693]</a></span>: document <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=4983\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4983'); return false;\" title=\"condor_submit should allow setting of attribs BEFORE submit is parsed\">#4983</a></span>  (By Karen Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Apr-16 10:59</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/ba32f59621ac12a30964ca56bfa0007d0ea3b6fd\">[44642]</a></span>: minor edit and LaTeX fix for new 8.3.5 version history items <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=4913\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper(